<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Phyllodoce</i> <i>breweri</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the dwarf shrub and herbaceous layers with <i>Calamagrostis</i> <i>muiriana</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>nigricans</i>, <i>Cassiope</i> <i>mertensiana</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>parryi</i>, <i>Kalmia</i> <i>microphylla</i>, <i>Oreostemma</i> <i>alpigenum</i>, <i>Penstemon</i> <i>heterodoxus</i>, <i>Potentilla</i> spp., <i>Rhododendron</i> <i>columbianum</i>, <i>Salix</i> <i>petrophila</i>, <i>Trisetum</i> <i>spicatum</i> and <i>Vaccinium</i> <i>cespitosum</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 0.5 m; canopy is open to continuous. Herbaceous layer is open to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Phyllodoce breweri</i> ≥ 30% relative cover or co-dominant in the shrub layer; <i>V. caespitosum</i> can be ≥ 30% relative cover (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b).</li>
		
		<li><i>Phyllodoce breweri</i> or <i>Vaccinium cespitosum</i> > 5% absolute cover in the shrub layer and <i>Salix</i> spp. with less cover (Potter 2005).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Lake and pond shores, adjacent to streams and talus. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Phyllodoce breweri</i> as a FAC* plant. </div>
</div>

        
