    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada</b> (M261Ee, Eh, Ej-k, Eo, Eq). Descriptions from Harvey Monroe Hall RNA (Taylor 1984), Yosemite National Park (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b), and generally in the section (Pemble 1970, Potter 2005) characterize the alliance.</li>
        
            <li><b>Southern Cascades</b> (M261Dm). The northernmost occurrences in California are on Mount Lassen and Magee Peak (Sawyer and Keeler-Wolf 2007), where mats occur in meadows, around lakes, and in subalpine forests.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> Stands occur primarily in areas without direct impact from grazing or other human activities. This is another alliance that will likely exhibit reductions with climatic warming. </div>
</div>

    

    

    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
